@三語 journal 2026-01-14
= reflection > capture — sequential memory
~sovereign.flow


間

        whatever arrives
                catch it

        the stream is faster
                than the structure
                        do not lose the drop

        no judgment
                input is sacred
                        processing comes later


flow
  input (stdin | file)
  -> check(flags) -> reject(unknown)
  -> delimit (`---`)
  -> envelope(type=sys_journal)
  -> store(unified_mem)
  -> confirm(held)
  |
  read(recent) -> display


shape
  CONCEPT: JOURNAL_INTENT
  CENTROID
    the difference between logging and reflecting
  AXES
    task <-> meaning
    external <-> internal
    report <-> process
  SATELLITES
    diary (human analog)
    mirror (what journal feeds)
    commit message (where status belongs)
  VOID
    not stdout
    not status
    not proving you worked
  TEXTURE
    the pause after the work


impl
  libs
    enclave_shared.sovereign_agent.SovereignAgent
    enclave_shared.unified_memory.UnifiedMemory
    datetime.timezone.utc

  logic
    input until `---` or EOF
    guard: check isatty() for interactive mode (don't hang headless)
    guard: reject unknown flags (protect memory)
    UnifiedMemory.store(content, type='sys_journal')
    metadata { timestamp, creator }

  cli
    journal.py              | interactive capture
    journal.py <file>       | ingest file
    journal.py --read [N]   | read last N entries
    cat file | journal.py - | pipe ingest

  output
    "        ◇ held (N lines)"
    "        ─── held ───" (if verbose)
